# deploy/config/.env.cloudflare.dev.example
# Cloudflare named-tunnel credentials. Copy to ".env.cloudflare.<env>" (e.g.
# ".env.cloudflare.dev") and fill. The filled file is GITIGNORED; only this
# .example is committed.
#
# Needed ONLY in named-tunnel mode (CLOUDFLARE_QUICK_TUNNEL=false in
# .env.provision.<env>); the quick-tunnel mode needs no Cloudflare account.
# These may also be supplied as environment variables instead of this file.
#
# Create the token at Cloudflare -> My Profile -> API Tokens -> Create Custom
# Token, scoped to the target zone:
#   - Zone : DNS : Edit
#   - Account : Cloudflare Tunnel : Edit
#
# Only CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN is strictly required — ACCOUNT_ID and ZONE_ID can be
# derived from the token via the Cloudflare API (GET /accounts, GET /zones).

CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
CLOUDFLARE_ZONE_ID=
